<div class='communityQuestionAndAnswer'>
<div class='communityQuestion'>
<div class='questionText'>
<a href="/questions/339164-trying-to-find-something-for-a-student-of">Trying to find something for a student of mine to read in the hospital as she undergoes her second round of chemo. Understandably, I want to stay away from books with young heroines dying. I&#39;ve had this book recommended to me as a good one for empowerment, but I cannot find any word on Ava&#39;s fate. Happy ending? Sad ending? Good idea for a young cancer patient? Any advice appreciated!</a>
</div>
<div class='communityQAFooter questionFooter'>
<ul class='questionFooterActions'>
<li class='footerItem like'>
<span class='likeItContainer' id='like_container_community_question_339164'><a id="like_count_community_question_339164" rel="nofollow" href="/rating/voters/339164?resource_type=CommunityQuestion"><span class="likesCount">6 likes</span></a>&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;<a rel="nofollow" class="jsLike like_it" href="https://www.goodreads.com/user/new?remember=true&amp;return_url=%2Fbook%2Fshow%2F18166936-the-strange-and-beautiful-sorrows-of-ava-lavender">like</a></span>

